# - Create a distance converter converting Km to miles
# - Take two inputs from user: Their first name and the distance in km
# - Print: Greet user by name and show km, and mile values
# - 1 mile is 1.609 kilometers
# - hint: use correct types for calculating and print
# - Did you capitalize the name

name = input('Enter Your First Name: ').capitalize()

Distance_km = float(input('Enter the distance in Kilometers: '))
Converted_Distance = float(Distance_km) / 1.609

print('Hello ' + name + '! Your Distance is ' + str(Distance_km) + ' kilometers.' + '! Your converted distance is ' + str(Converted_Distance) + ' miles!')


